<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Durban May 2 SAPA -- Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] 
leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi was at work on Monday [2 May], 
having partly recovered from a serious bout of influenza, 
KwaZulu government spokesman Mr T C Memela said. Mr Memela said 
a caucus meeting of the KwaZulu legislative assembly was planned 
for Wednesday when the elections and the way forward would be 
discussed. 
  The homeland government, Mr Memela added, was adopting a 
"wait and see" attitude towards the integration of public 
administrations in KwaZulu/Natal and the inauguration of the new 
provincial government. 

