<H3> <TI>   DP Leader Disappointed by Provincial Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DP Leader Disappointed by Provincial Results </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0205102694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0600 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0205102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Party [DP] has expressed 
disappointment at its provincial results. DP leader Zach de 
Beer said at the IEC's [Independent Electoral Commission] 
headquarters at Gallagher's Estate that the results were much 
worse than expected. He attributed his party's poor performance 
to National Party [NP] propaganda which had called on the 
electorate to vote for the NP to prevent domination by the 
ANC-communist party alliance. He said the DP was not 
considering merging with another party because there were no 
other attractive prospects. The DP would continue to play an 
important role as watchdog over human rights and democracy. 

</TEXT>

