<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Missing Ballot Papers Found in PWV Warehouse </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0105131494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1307 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0105131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg May 1 SAPA -- Hundreds of thousands of 
missing ballot papers have been found in two warehouses in the 
PWV [Pretoria, Witwatersrand, Vereeniging] area, the Independent 
Electoral Commission [IEC] said on Sunday [1 May]. 
  IEC Commissioner Dikgang Moseneke said people had been 
subpoenaed to answer questions about the papers found in 
warehouses on the East Rand and West Rand. Investigations were 
continuing, Mr Moseneke said. A shortage of ballot papers in 
the PWV caused long queues at polling stations in the region on 
Tuesday and Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

