<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Tanzania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Burundi Refugees Required To Surrender Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Burundi Refugees Required To Surrender Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0305194494 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 
1000 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0305194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Swahili </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Refugees entering from Burundi are required to 
surrender their weapons to the head of their respective camps 
immediately, in order to ensure their security and that of their 
countrymen. This was a directive issued yesterday by Kibondo 
District Commissioner (Thomas Kingi), when he was explaining to 
refugees at (Kamomba) Camp that they are required to respect all 
of this country's laws when they arrive. Ndugu (Kingi) said 
that the refugees who decide to return to Burundi will be given 
their weapons back, after they satisfy their respective refugee 
camp heads that they acquired those weapons legally. The 
district commissioner also said that refugees who want to go out 
of their camps and return later, and those who decide to go back 
to Burundi, should report to the heads of the camps instead of 
running away. Those found to be violating the law shall be 
prosecuted. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

