<H3> <TI>   Taylor To Send Team to Monrovia for Talks With LPC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Taylor To Send Team to Monrovia for Talks With LPC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0305203294 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1400 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0305203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A news just coming in says: In furtherance of the 
ongoing peace process in Liberia, the leader of the National 
Patriotic Front of Liberia [NPFL], Mr. Charles Gankay Taylor, 
has opted to send a high-powered delegation to Monrovia to hold 
discussions with the Liberian Peace Council [LPC], aimed at 
resolving the conflict in Rivercess and parts of Sinoe County. 
In a press release today, Mr. Taylor said while the NPFL is 
fully aware that the LPC is not a party to the Cotonou Peace 
Accord, yet because of the love he has for the Liberian people 
and his desire for peace and national reconciliation, a 
delegation will leave Gbarnga shortly to hold discussions in 
Monrovia. The NPFL leader is, therefore, urging the special 
representative to Liberia and head of UNOMIL [UN Observer 
Mission to Liberia], Ambassador Gordon-Somers, to provide full 
security protection and sponsorship for the ensuing talks. 

</TEXT>

