<H3> <TI>   ECOMOG, UNOMIL Blamed for Slow Pace of Peace Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ECOMOG, UNOMIL Blamed for Slow Pace of Peace Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0305222694 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1400 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0305222694 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Citizens in the rest of the country say ECOMOG 
[Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring 
Group] and United Nations Observer Mission in Liberia [UNOMIL] 
are responsible for the slow pace in the Liberian peace process. 
In a survey conducted by LCN [Liberia Communications Network] 
News in Gbarnga, the citizens said, although fighting is taking 
place between the so-called Liberian Peace Council and the NPFL 
[National Patriotic Front of Liberia] in the southeast of the 
country, ECOMOG and UNOMIL have not moved in to stop the 
fighting. 

</TEXT>

