<H3> <TI>   Three UN Soldiers Killed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three UN Soldiers Killed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405092894 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
0842 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Three soldiers with the UN Mission in Rwanda 
[UNAMIR] were wounded on Tuesday [3 May] night during shelling 
of Kigali airport. A UNAMIR spokesman announced this as violent 
fighting was continuing in Kigali. Mortar shells which hit the 
airport were launched by the Rwandan Patriotic Front forces, who 
were responding to shots fired by the government forces. 

</TEXT>

