<H3> <TI>   Viljoen Puts Damper on Cabinet Post Offer </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Viljoen Puts Damper on Cabinet Post Offer </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0305151994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0305151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] General Constand Viljoen of the Freedom Front has 
put a damper on expectations that he could accept a cabinet 
post, saying that his real job is to be with his people and to 
find a land area for Afrikaners who choose to be together. 
However, Gen. Viljoen said that he would have to discuss the 
issue with Mr. Nelson Mandela before deciding finally. Last 
night, Mr. Mandela praised Gen. Viljoen, describing him as a 
worthy South African who would make a contribution to the 
government of national unity. It was later rumored that he 
could even be appointed Minister of Defense. Projections for the 
National Assembly at this stage show the Freedom Front taking 13 
seats, seven short of the 20 required for a cabinet post. 

</TEXT>

