<H3> <TI>   To Be Included in Defense Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    To Be Included in Defense Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0305151694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1440 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0305151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria May 3 SAPA -- The Pan-Africanist Congress 
[PAC] has been admitted as a member of the Transitional 
Executive Council [TEC]. According to a proclamation by 
President F. W. de Klerk in a special government gazette of 
Tuesday, the PAC is now a participant. 
  Although TEC sittings have finished -- its management 
committee may meet on Monday -- the move will give the PAC a 
seat on the joint military command council which is planning the 
new South African National Defence Force [SANDF]. 
  The PAC will now be entitled to have its Azanian People's 
Liberation Army cadres included in the new SANDF. 

</TEXT>

