<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suzman: Halt Due to `Delay All Over' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Suzman: Halt Due to `Delay All Over' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0305180594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1750 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0305180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg May 3 SAPA -- Independent Electoral 
Commission [IEC] representative Helen Suzman on Tuesday [3 May] 
night said a delay in incoming results was because of a "delay 
all over", but she denied serious problems. The only problem 
was "one or two" counting stations which had requested help with 
reconciliation, she said. Asked why there was a breakdown in 
the flow of results, Mrs Suzman responded: "It is because there 
is a delay all over." 
  Reliable sources said earlier a halt to all further election 
results issues had been called, and might last 24 hours. 

</TEXT>

