<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Accelerated' Vote Counting Procedure Announced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Accelerated' Vote Counting Procedure Announced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0305183594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1828 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0305183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg May 3 SAPA -- The Independent Electoral 
Commission [IEC] was revamping its counting procedures overnight 
with election results expected to flow again on Wednesday [4 
May] morning, the IEC said Tuesday night. 
  The vote counting was to be accelerated by entering the 
total 
number of votes recorded at counting stations as the basis for 
accumulating national and provincial tallies. This would 
replace the old system, which involved the entry into the count 
of batches of 2-3000 votes from the counting stations as the 
figures came in. 
  "This changeover will take place during the course of the 
night and results will continue to flow during the course of the 
morning," the IEC statement said. The commission stressed it 
had not stopped counting votes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

