<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   KwaZulu Assembly To Discuss ANC Claim </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KwaZulu Assembly To Discuss ANC Claim </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0405123194 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0405123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A caucus of the KwaZulu Legislative Assembly is to 
meet in Ulundi today to discuss claims of electoral fraud in 
KwaZulu-Natal. A spokesman for the assembly said there would 
also be discussions on the future of legislative assembly 
members after the inauguration of the new provincial legislature 
in Pietermaritzburg. He said King Goodwill Zwelithini planned to 
address the meeting. 
  The IEC [Independent Electoral Commission] said earlier that 
it was investigating allegations by the ANC of massive election 
fraud by the IFP in KwaZulu-Natal. IFP [Inkatha Freedom Party] 
spokesman Frank Mdlalose has denied the ANC allegations. He 
told REUTER that he was not aware of any fraud orchestrated by 
the IFP. Commenting on the IEC investigation, Dr. Mdlalose said 
he doubted its impartiality because there were too many ANC 
sympathizers in the commission. An ANC official in 
KwaZulu-Natal said the party had information that ballot boxes 
from IFP strongholds in rural areas of the region had been 
tampered with. 

</TEXT>

