<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buthelezi Relieved ANC Dropping Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buthelezi Relieved ANC Dropping Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0405140094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1342 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0405140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulundi May 4 SAPA -- Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] 
President Mangosuthu Buthelezi said he had learnt with great 
relief on Wednesday [4 May] afternoon the African National 
Congress had withdrawn charges of electoral fraud against his 
party. The IFP leader told an impromptu Ulundi press briefing he 
would stand by the election results if the other parties did so. 
  Mr Buthelezi said it was "very mean" of the ANC to have made 
a mountain out of a molehill over claimed IFP irregularities in 
the voting process. He said he was concerned about the anger 
which could have generated. 
  Mr Buthelezi said he had entered the all-race elections on 
the understanding that he would stand by the results. 
  In spite of reservations about the process "I don't think 
there is any possibility of me turning around, rejecting the 
results". 
  He said that would be construed as sour grapes. 

</TEXT>

