<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Goldstone Releases Report on Eskom Weapons Sale to KwaZulu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Goldstone Releases Report on Eskom Weapons Sale to KwaZulu </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0405124694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0405124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Goldstone Commission has released its report on 
the preliminary inquiry into the attempted purchase of firearms 
by the KwaZulu Government from Eskom [Electricity Supply 
Commission]. The commission said it was disturbing that the 
commissioner of police had issued an export permit for the 
weapons without realizing the sensitivity of the matter. The 
commission found that the sale of 1,000 semi-automatic rifles to 
the KwaZulu Police had not been authorized by the management of 
Eskom, but that the sale had been arranged without authority by 
an employee of the company. The commission said it was 
satisfied that the National Intelligence Service had had nothing 
to do with the transaction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

