<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   State of Emergency Lifted for W. Transvaal Towns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State of Emergency Lifted for W. Transvaal Towns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0305143594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1311 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0305143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Potchefstroom May 3 SAPA -- The state of emergency 
imposed on 15 Western Transvaal towns last week was lifted on 
Tuesday [3 May] morning. Deputy regional commissioner of police 
Brig Izak Smalman said the state of emergency declared on April 
28 in the magisterial districts of Potchefstroom, Swartruggens, 
Marico, Lichtenburg, Coligny, Ventersdorp, Delareyville, 
Schweizer-Reneke, Wolmeransstad, Bloemhof, Klerksdorp, Koster, 
Christiana, Oberholzer and Rustenburg had been lifted. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

