<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANC Election Lead Said Affecting Financial Market </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ANC Election Lead Said Affecting Financial Market </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0405124594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0405124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Market nervousness at the possibility of a 
two-thirds majority, once final election results are known, has 
contributed to the commercial rand losing more than five cents 
against the dollar. The rand has slipped to nearly 3.605 rands 
against the dollar, a currency which is in short supply on the 
local market. The rand has also lost five cents against 
sterling to 5.42 rands. The financial rand has weakened by 11 
cents to trade at 4.71 rands to the dollar. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

