<H3> <TI>   Date for First National Assembly Session Changed to 9 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Date for First National Assembly Session Changed to 9 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0305173894 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 
1600 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0305173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  Afrikaans </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just heard that the first session of the 
National Assembly will only take place next Monday [9 May] in 
Cape Town and not, as initially planned, on the 6 May. The 
Transitional Executive Council's management committee has 
decided that the first meeting of the provincial legislature 
will be held on Saturday, 7 May, at various meeting points. 
This decision by the management committee was taken on the 
basis of information received by the Independent Electoral 
Commission. The change of date will not affect the inauguration 
ceremony for the state president at the Union Buildings in 
Pretoria on Tuesday, 10 May. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

