<F P=101> Uganda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Museveni, UN Envoy Discuss Rwandan Mediation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Museveni, UN Envoy Discuss Rwandan Mediation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0405210194 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 1900 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0405210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Yoweri Museveni has had a meeting with 
the special representative of the UN secretary general in 
Rwanda, Dr. Jacques-Roger Booh-Booh, who is also the UN under 
secretary general. The meeting took place at the president's 
office in Kampala. Dr. Booh-Booh delivered a special message 
from the UN secretary general, Dr. Butrus Butrus-Ghali, and 
afterwards briefed the president on the situation in Rwanda and 
informed the president that the United Nations is carrying out a 
wide range of consultations to see how best the UN can 
contribute to the alleviation of the suffering of the people in 
Rwanda. 
  Dr. Booh-Booh also briefed the president on the present 
efforts in Arusha aimed at bringing the Rwandan groups to 
dialogue. President Museveni welcomed the efforts to promote 
dialogue between the Rwandan groups and expressed deep regret at 
the killings and suffering taking place in Rwanda. He pledged 
support to the initiatives to promote dialogue and expressed 
hope that such could result into a solution. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

