<H3> <TI>   Buthelezi on Election Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buthelezi on Election Results </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0405195694 Johannesburg SABC CCV Television Network in 
Enhglish 1900 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0405195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC CCV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Enhglish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Inkatha Freedom Party President Mangusuthu Buthelezi 
says he had never tried to have two options with regard to the 
acceptance of the election resutls, but that his reservations 
were centered around allegations of irregularities during the 
election. He spoke to our correspondent at Ulundi today. 
  [Begin Buthelexi recording] When we went to the elections, 
it 
was under the understanding that we would accept the results of 
the elections, and the only reservation that I had was because 
of all the irregularities that were taking place, that made me 
reserve my position and say that, you know, well, let's wait and 
see what the outcome is. But I don't think that there's any 
possibility that I could turn around and say that I don't accept 
the results of the elections, if everyone else accepts them. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

