<H3> <TI>   International Reaction to Elections, Mandela Victory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    International Reaction to Elections, Mandela Victory </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kozyrev Comments </H4>

<F P=102> LD0505000094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2202 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505000094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov and </F>
ITAR- TASS correspondent Georgiy Shelenkov] 
  [Text] Cairo, 5 May -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev, who is here on a visit, made the following press 
statement to the ITAR-TASS correspondents: 
  "There has been an epoch-making event in the Republic of 
South Africa that has put the country's development onto a 
democratic footing -- namely, the country's first-ever universal 
elections. 
  "The world community, which has for decades been 
persistently 
striving for a restoration of racial and social justice in the 
RSA, today notes that this goal has been achieved. For its 
part, Russia, which has invariably supported all the 
constructive efforts of the South African Government, parties, 
and public organizations along the path of democratic 
transformations, shares with everyone a feeling of deep 
satisfaction at the results of these efforts. 
  "We believe that favorable prospects are opening up for the 
harmonious economic and social development of the peoples of 
South Africa. Much will depend on the readiness of all the 
country's political forces for constructive interaction similar 
to what they have shown during the period of preparations for 
the elections. 
  "Russia expresses its readiness to cooperate with the new 
democratic South Africa and hopes that the good relations that 
have been formed between our countries and peoples will in the 
coming period be further developed in the interests of universal 
peace and prosperity." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

