<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   MK Members Receiving Training at Air Force Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MK Members Receiving Training at Air Force Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0505081394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2116 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0505081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria May 4 SAPA -- Two hundred Umkhonto we Sizwe 
[Spear of the Nation; ANC military wing -- MK] instructors are 
undergoing "induction training" at the South African Air Force 
Gymnasium in Pretoria in preparation for the integration of MK 
with the National Defence Force. 
  The South African National Defence Force's [SANDF] internal 
communication bulletin this week said the two-week course, to 
end on May 13, would enable the African National Congress 
military wing members to give induction training to their 
colleagues in assembly-point areas, "thus contributing to a 
smoother process of integration". 
  The group is being trained in military terminology, military 
law, personal financial planning and military etiquette, 
including mess etiquette. 
  The bulletin said the course would overcome any shortcomings 
in military skills among the trainees, adding that their basic 
training might have been different to that approved by the Joint 
Military Co-ordinating Council of the SANDF. "This will ensure 
that they suffer no relative disadvantage in relation to the 
members of the other forces involved in the integration 
process," it said. "This is a pure orientation course, therefore 
no formal evaluation will be done." 
  The bulletin said the trainees would be under the command of 
the officer commanding the gymnasium and a high standard of 
discipline would be expected. The bulletin also said other MK 
members were being trained in ceremonial drill to prepare them 
to form part of the guard of honour at the inauguration of the 
new president on May 10. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
