<H3> <TI>   General Strike Spreads; Soldiers Drafted To Work </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General Strike Spreads; Soldiers Drafted To Work </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0505062594 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 1830 GMT 4 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0505062594 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville Africa No. 1 </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The general strike urged by the Federation of 
Chadian Trade Unions and followed by Chadian civil servants 
since 26 April in order to compel the government to sign a 
social pact is still being observed. It spread yesterday to the 
Posts and Telecommunications Corporation where employees have 
stopped work. Journalists and technical personnel in the public 
media are also on strike so radio and television are carrying 
only minimal programming. The government has consequently asked 
soldiers to operate these technical installations. 

</TEXT>

