<H3> <TI>   RPF Chairman Reiterates Position on Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RPF Chairman Reiterates Position on Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0405171594 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in English to 
Rwanda 1100 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0405171594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] has no 
intention to negotiate with the illegitimate government in 
Rwanda. The chairman of the RPF, Colonel Alexis Kanyarengwe, 
has been in Tanzania to explain the RPF position that what is 
needed in Rwanda now is not negotiations and mediation, but 
Rwanda needs material aid. Rwanda also needs to bring to 
justice those who are responsible for the massacres that have 
been taking place in Rwanda. 
  The RPF chairman said that Rwanda does not need another 
Arusha peace agreement. The peace agreement was signed after 12 
months of negotiations only to be derailed by the same people 
who are now calling for negotiations with the RPF. These are 
the members of the self-imposed government in Rwanda. [passage 
omitted] 
  It's only yesterday that this government murdered 21 orphans 
and three Red Cross workers who were taking care of the orphans 
in Butare Prefecture. While they call for negotiations with the 
RPF, members of the illegitimate government in Rwanda are 
holding the entire nation hostage. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

