<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   10 May Declared Public Holiday </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    10 May Declared Public Holiday </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0405165794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 1600 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0405165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet has decided to declare 10 May, the date 
of the inauguration of the new president, a public holiday. The 
cabinet said in a statement it was well aware that the recent 
series of unscheduled public holidays had created serious 
disruptions and problems for organized commerce and industry. 
However, it had received strong recommendations in favor of the 
day being a public holiday from the Transitional Executive 
Council and the National Inauguration Committee. 

</TEXT>

