<F P=101> Burundi </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Leonard Nyangoma Resigns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister Leonard Nyangoma Resigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405185894 Paris Radio France International in French 1830 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Burundi Leonard Nyangoma, minister of the 
interior and security, has resigned. This has just been 
announced this evening by Mr. Kanyenkiko, the prime minister. 
The minister of the interior has been abroad for several weeks. 
He was accused by the Burundi Armed Forces of being behind the 
armed gangs they have been clashing with for several weeks in 
the northern outskirts of Bujumbura. 

</TEXT>

