<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Endorses Call For UN Action </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Butrus-Ghali Endorses Call For UN Action </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0605200994 Nairobi KNA in English 1640 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0605200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi KNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Dar es Salaam, 6 May (KNA/PANA) -- The UN 
Secretary General, Butrus Butrus-Ghali, has endorsed an appeal 
by former Tanzanian president, Mwalimu Julius Nyerere, calling 
for urgent action to resolve the Rwandan situation. [passage 
omitted] 
  In a press statement made available to Shihata, the UN 
secretar - general said he had given full support to the appeal, 
according to a press statement issued today by the UN 
Information Centre in Dar es Salaam. [passage omitted] 
  Meanwhile, the UNHCR has said it urgently needed $38.5 
million to provide humanitarian aid for 250,000 Rwandan refugees 
in Tanzania over the next three months. Aid workers have been 
battling torrential rains and sanitation problems to ease the 
plight of the refugees, who are crowded into makeshift camp near 
Ngara. 

</TEXT>

