<H3> <TI>   ULIMO Frontline Commanders Agree to Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ULIMO Frontline Commanders Agree to Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0705154694 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0705154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Monrovia Radio ELBC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Krahn and Mandingo frontline commanders of ULIMO 
[United Liberation Movement for Democracy in Liberia] have 
agreed to cease fire [words indistinct]. They have also agreed 
that all roads within ULIMO-controlled areas be under the 
control of ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States 
Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] and be open for free passage for 
all persons. 
  These agreements were reached yesterday at the end of a 
meeting between the two groups at ECOMOG headquarters in 
Monrovia. The joint communique, signed by both groups, also 
says that the hierarchy of ULIMO leadership will meet in 
Monrovia Monday [9 May] under the auspices of ECOMOG and UNOMIL 
[UN Observer Mission in Liberia] to effectively reunite the 
ULIMO family. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

