<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fighting in Kigali Prevents UN Plane From Landing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fighting in Kigali Prevents UN Plane From Landing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0905121594 Paris AFP in English 1152 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0905121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Nairobi, 9 May (AFP) -- Fierce fighting erupted 
in Kigali on Monday [9 May] between government troops and rebels 
of the Rwandan Patriotic Front (RPF) forcing a United Nations 
plane heading to the wartorn country to return to Nairobi. The 
Hercules C-130 from the Canadian Air Force had left Nairobi at 
10:00 A.M. (0700 GMT) but midway through the flight was ordered 
to return to Nairobi because of the battles in Kigali. 
  Abdul Kabia, spokesman for the UN Assistance Mission in 
Rwanda (UNAMIR) said the fighting began at 0800 GMT in various 
parts of the capital including the military camp in Kanombe, 
near the Kigali airport and the rebel headquarters. He said one 
mortar fell on the airport runway but did not cause any 
injuries. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

